text: ...why, exactly, is it that films marketed towards a female audience seem almost desperate? I mean, most targeted media wears its intentions on its sleeve, sure. Big dumb masculine films want to get testosterone pumping, flashy pointless garbage is trying to distract kids for an hour and a half, and what have you, and there's nothing wrong with any of that. But whenever I see anything considered a 'Chick Flick', it always comes across kind of insulting towards womens intelligence :/  Maybe I just don't understand this and never will, what with being the owner of a 6/10 dick and balls, but whenever I try to contort my brain enough to imagine I'm a woman in the audience and this crap is trying to sell me to go see it, I can't help feeling patronized and insulted.

Total waste of time and money, do yourselves a favour and skip it.
